metadata.name: Provence #200
metadata.description:
The south of France namely the Provence has a cultural history of being an inspiration for impressionists and post-impressionists in the past.
For me personally the Provence is the place i was spending long, peaceful holidays as a child within beautiful nature.
This work does not so much aim for being realistic, rather than give an impression or feeling for this wonderful landscape. 
There are just a few different elements and concepts and yet there is variety of fascinating results.
I really hope you will enjoy your minting.

Notes:
STARTUP AND RENDERING MAY TAKE SOME TIME. (Up to 1min)
Code was written in typescript.
The only used libraries were chroma.js and simplex-noise

metadata.description:
You may find them deep underwater. Nobody really knows what are they. Are they strange mysterious jellyfishes Are they aliens Or maybe alien jellyfishes came through the space right into our oceans Let's call them Jellyfishaliens!!!
Try to find one yourself and make a unique photo, but beware they are very quick and may disappear before you are ready to make a shot! But this will be rewarding and you will enjoy unbelievable game of glowing colours of that mysterious creatures. If you are lucky enough, you may catch more than one!

metadata.name: Frost's Road #148
metadata.description:
Do you take the less traveled road and dispel the wonder of what might have been?  Or, do you preserve the mystery by gazing down the overgrown, winding path savoring the speculation--never to be disappointed or have your wonder sated?

Frost's Road celebrates the obvious and enigmatic themes of Frost's poem, "The Road Not Taken."  A generative path to nowhere? Or someplace special?  Frost's Road subtly captures the obviousness of a vacant path, and the questions that lingers about why is that.

Created with p5js.

Press the Down Arrow to save the frame as a png.
Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode.
Output Size: 995 x 1080.
